{"title":"UTD. Mioclonias-2025","guid":"","filepath":"/Users/criaah/Vault/📚 Resources/Mapas-Mentales/Entidades clínicas/Neurología/UTD. Mioclonias-2025.smmx","root":{"id":"0","parent":"-1","text":"Mioclonias","guid":"ZAu6pKi0o4D7vY8RoDHO0w","children":[{"id":"1","parent":"0","text":"1. Introducción\\Ny definición","guid":"","children":[{"id":"2","parent":"1","text":"• Mioclonus = Movimientos involuntarios breves y bruscos (contracción o inhibición muscular).","guid":"ODCC-ljFnbaFOdoueTjMXg","children":[]},{"id":"3","parent":"1","text":"• Positivo → Por contracción muscular.","guid":"XNAE_m8gpn8idPRNwFOEtg","children":[]},{"id":"4","parent":"1","text":"• Negativo → Por inhibición muscular (ej. asterixis).","guid":"lMUaX76EfJSVd2wZ6iBBEw","children":[]},{"id":"5","parent":"1","text":"• Se describe como sacudidas, espasmos o temblores.","guid":"UnnolZs6Dmq37rwJOoStpQ","children":[]},{"id":"6","parent":"1","text":"• Tiene múltiples etiologías y mecanismos fisiopatológicos.","guid":"KYYylL2-96c8MI2Fvht-Rg","children":[]}]},{"id":"7","parent":"0","text":"2. Clasificación\\Nanatómica y fisiológica","guid":"","children":[{"id":"8","parent":"7","text":"Se basa en la localización del mecanismo fisiológico subyacente.","guid":"oo15rzu8iTtKDPR8WubZ4g","children":[]},{"id":"9","parent":"7","text":"A. Mioclonus\\Ncortical","guid":"iJn72eDe5sD5Cl6SMeEsRg","children":[{"id":"10","parent":"9","text":"• Origen: Descarga focal en la corteza sensorimotora.","guid":"oETay1qiULnxuuJngVDq3g","children":[]},{"id":"11","parent":"9","text":"• Causa: Falla en la inhibición neuronal (corteza motora y sensitiva primaria).","guid":"NaKOl81ojnoo8WFsp2F_ZQ","children":[]},{"id":"12","parent":"9","text":"• Tipos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"13","parent":"12","text":"• Reflejo cortical → Respuesta exagerada a estímulos somatosensoriales.","guid":"UdbWIDUqr2FV_PdVeenXPQ","children":[]},{"id":"14","parent":"12","text":"• De acción → Relacionado con activación muscular.","guid":"tYxfnEsxpYdu23RXrnWoJQ","children":[]},{"id":"15","parent":"12","text":"• En reposo → Asociado a crisis motoras focales.","guid":"6BbVePEVbHlo9UYZHgjTxQ","children":[]},{"id":"16","parent":"12","text":"• Combinaciones → Puede ocurrir en cualquier contexto.","guid":"LnnPlHqvTq_KPOY9uhP-FQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"17","parent":"9","text":"• Características:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"18","parent":"17","text":"• Distribución focal o multifocal (según localización de la disfunción).","guid":"K-7muV2IjiJL0ygmPd9PTQ","children":[]},{"id":"19","parent":"17","text":"• Puede evolucionar a mioclonus generalizado y crisis tónico-clónicas.","guid":"PN-8yYDPQTpVfYSK4SQqkQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"20","parent":"9","text":"• Mecanismo incierto →\\NPosibles vías implicadas:","guid":"Rfs-gSeLSsAG7paTqWiUqw","children":[{"id":"21","parent":"20","text":"• GABAérgicas.","guid":"sIVNGMe25Ej03KZi2oXzPw","children":[]},{"id":"22","parent":"20","text":"• Serotoninérgicas.","guid":"BmMJD4j5qJ9nOl5NLwijIQ","children":[]},{"id":"23","parent":"20","text":"• Circuitos cerebelosos.","guid":"-0IcjMWs841mz-cPFrvsDw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"24","parent":"7","text":"B. Mioclonus\\Ncórtico-subcortical","guid":"0-P5za1xQXKcBTjQbOGg_w","children":[{"id":"25","parent":"24","text":"• Mecanismo central en crisis mioclónicas epilépticas (ej. epilepsia mioclónica juvenil [JME]).","guid":"7PWfA2K5dWLKjqIyWTXq-g","children":[]},{"id":"26","parent":"24","text":"• Origen: Acoplamiento anómalo entre redes talámicas y corticales → Hiperexcitabilidad neuronal.","guid":"cgLP5kyi8B7gVX1Z_dnrUQ","children":[]},{"id":"27","parent":"24","text":"• Características:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"28","parent":"27","text":"• Descargas paroxísticas y oscilatorias.","guid":"gfXkipXPPL-8ebeNbMJEcg","children":[]},{"id":"29","parent":"27","text":"• Mioclonus generalizado o bisíncrono.","guid":"XvOBthZbUUHJgBWqcYG2Ww","children":[]},{"id":"30","parent":"27","text":"• Relación con crisis de ausencia y JME.","guid":"69YG_ppDz9kf27XhjObi-w","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"31","parent":"7","text":"C. Mioclonus subcortical-no\\Nsegmentario","guid":"wBCSnnvKvKMaPf4V7sNHVw","children":[{"id":"32","parent":"31","text":"• Origen: Subcortical, con manifestaciones extendidas más allá del segmento de origen.","guid":"QrU3L_qp0wRdKVKhakH7ig","children":[]},{"id":"33","parent":"31","text":"• Tipos\\Nprincipales:","guid":"0iziCljtA-3IUCvE7ZtgwA","children":[{"id":"34","parent":"33","text":"• Mioclonus reticular-reflejo → Actividad anómala en tronco encefálico con propagación bilateral.","guid":"kx0Nlv_vTQHx65M2FUuOJg","children":[]},{"id":"35","parent":"33","text":"• Mioclonus propioespinal → Actividad en médula espinal con propagación rostral y caudal.","guid":"Gw3RenZPGVU968xkUpq_BQ","children":[]},{"id":"36","parent":"33","text":"• Mioclonus-distonía → Afecta cabeza, cuello, torso y brazos.","guid":"I7Fav4daGzbjyFgbZGoRGg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"37","parent":"7","text":"D. Mioclonus\\Nsegmentario","guid":"y4neeFAWrVUEZxcEgNnjQw","children":[{"id":"38","parent":"37","text":"• Origen: Segmentos específicos del tronco encefálico o médula espinal.","guid":"qb9Dy4OVB2L441YiCjbDTA","children":[]},{"id":"39","parent":"37","text":"• Características:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"40","parent":"39","text":"• Oscilaciones motoras más lentas que el temblor.","guid":"6xE3phJX5mUlpGvo9u32Qg","children":[]}]},{"id":"41","parent":"37","text":"• Ejemplos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"42","parent":"41","text":"• Mioclonus palatino.","guid":"sXL-4syzvfOCRcJfhICffQ","children":[]},{"id":"43","parent":"41","text":"• Mioclonus segmentario espinal.","guid":"cP12ni2_n07bZApYhrKcag","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"44","parent":"7","text":"E. Mioclonus\\Nperiférico","guid":"rc1igqETiRu2ShTOn2ffvw","children":[{"id":"45","parent":"44","text":"• Causa: Lesión en el sistema nervioso periférico → Descargas motoras hiperactivas.","guid":"6YCoRgu4x-xaPBZHmwTXmQ","children":[]},{"id":"46","parent":"44","text":"• Ejemplo: Espasmo hemifacial.","guid":"Fs8ht0r9kh3lP7KrTRr8WQ","children":[]},{"id":"47","parent":"44","text":"• Posible reorganización central, pero mecanismo no definido.","guid":"G03GmU74XghTcO49v5cZJw","children":[]}]},{"id":"48","parent":"7","text":"→ Esta clasificación permite localizar lesiones, orientar diagnóstico y guiar tratamiento.","guid":"nTk-plrva6_FpGCr5d2T-Q","children":[]}]},{"id":"49","parent":"0","text":"1. Epidemiología","guid":"","children":[{"id":"50","parent":"49","text":"• Incidencia: 1.3 casos/100,000 personas-año (Condado de Olmsted, Minnesota).","guid":"nj6H2AdbImp5yJssF8Eufw","children":[]},{"id":"51","parent":"49","text":"• Prevalencia de por vida: 8. 6/100,000 habitantes (1990).","guid":"_7o9cGEhJV2i9Mza017CrA","children":[]},{"id":"52","parent":"49","text":"• Tipos más comunes:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"53","parent":"52","text":"• Mioclonus secundario (sintomático) → 72%.","guid":"5yCYfyZpXOpRNVS1NMt-Dw","children":[]},{"id":"54","parent":"52","text":"• Mioclonus epiléptico → 17%.","guid":"dBw1HHqN7UdZPG7-p-mt9g","children":[]},{"id":"55","parent":"52","text":"• Mioclonus esencial → 11%.","guid":"l2Sc1rSc5Gp6EblTLGw4cg","children":[]}]},{"id":"56","parent":"49","text":"• Causas\\Nfrecuentes:","guid":"dws4snr1j4_RnZTFn8Dgbw","children":[{"id":"57","parent":"56","text":"• Estados posthipóxicos (síndrome de Lance-Adams).","guid":"GVZ8WWLRHH8OGOgiFZOB8Q","children":[]},{"id":"58","parent":"56","text":"• Enfermedades neurodegenerativas.","guid":"dU9UZRSJQ4pu5h9OwFgXLA","children":[]},{"id":"59","parent":"56","text":"• Síndromes epilépticos.","guid":"cicdYhY42R-h8IoA6ZYzrA","children":[]},{"id":"60","parent":"56","text":"• Tóxico-metabólico y fármacos (especialmente en hospitales).","guid":"X3JnwmYIo4TuF8YyRa1avw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"61","parent":"0","text":"2. Clasificación\\Netiológica (Marsden)","guid":"","children":[{"id":"62","parent":"61","text":"→ Cuatro categorías principales","guid":"Y5UJK29v51xwAXQblCeFiQ","children":[]},{"id":"63","parent":"61","text":"A. Mioclonus\\Nfisiológico","guid":"p-onuD4o9RHi0j0qLRNvYw","children":[{"id":"64","parent":"63","text":"• Fenómeno normal en individuos sanos.","guid":"kd7kOWRrGBPbndqeTdtY0w","children":[]},{"id":"65","parent":"63","text":"• Sin discapacidad ni hallazgos anormales en examen físico.","guid":"6NNC-TBer7mGoy-06ZW-yA","children":[]},{"id":"66","parent":"63","text":"• Ejemplos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"67","parent":"66","text":"• Sacudidas en la transición del sueño (hipnagogias).","guid":"FWe7DD0SPcgwiPHN377nMg","children":[]},{"id":"68","parent":"66","text":"• Mioclonus inducido por ansiedad o ejercicio.","guid":"Vnz5wXhMwquvIVL0SmmVnA","children":[]},{"id":"69","parent":"66","text":"• Hipo (singultus).","guid":"3Ry4qUw3QQada27omMWSNg","children":[]},{"id":"70","parent":"66","text":"• Mioclonus infantil benigno al alimentarse.","guid":"LtBDdarNVs6snoRguevi5Q","children":[]},{"id":"71","parent":"66","text":"• Tipos de sacudidas\\Nen el sueño:","guid":"GTnaJuGib6XiRnl3LqGaWw","children":[{"id":"72","parent":"71","text":"• Parciales → Multifocales, en músculos distales.","guid":"sXbD-voXRVZV3rUxdXPYSw","children":[]},{"id":"73","parent":"71","text":"• Masivas → Generalizadas, en tronco y músculos proximales.","guid":"glpksgf27_38W2NJLW6NNg","children":[]},{"id":"74","parent":"71","text":"• Movimientos periódicos de extremidades en el sueño (PLMS) → Dorsiflexión repetitiva de pies y dedos.","guid":"EBpL_HsRbbUDJJb3v6vwRw","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"75","parent":"61","text":"B. Mioclonus\\Nesencial","guid":"BT5qooN8Eh1bVko5teMrpg","children":[{"id":"76","parent":"75","text":"• Único hallazgo clínico predominante → Leve discapacidad.","guid":"1XYiN2tVrWDgiVuWlNRTzg","children":[]},{"id":"77","parent":"75","text":"• Progresión lenta o ausente.","guid":"mfMijQkc86K-z3WERLUXgQ","children":[]},{"id":"78","parent":"75","text":"• Cognición normal.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"79","parent":"75","text":"• Tipos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"80","parent":"79","text":"• Esporádico (idiopático) → Heterogéneo en distribución y factores desencadenantes.","guid":"KXInWsgID7Y6hoJHjBWJIQ","children":[]},{"id":"81","parent":"79","text":"• Heredado (autosómico\\Ndominante, inicio <20 años):","guid":"UHf2aKdjBAaFacqtjPE4lg","children":[{"id":"82","parent":"81","text":"• Curso benigno → Compatible con vida activa y normal.","guid":"3Zj7SURFzzjxuuW5K9jyYQ","children":[]},{"id":"83","parent":"81","text":"• Afecta brazos y músculos axiales.","guid":"sHLhJVD5NulF520H0JmK7g","children":[]},{"id":"84","parent":"81","text":"• Disminuye con alcohol.","guid":"05c6Z0YYl5kR7Qd2miBYew","children":[]},{"id":"85","parent":"81","text":"• Asociado a mioclonus-distonia.","guid":"4Zu8XcqA0oTf8--q0w5pXw","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"86","parent":"75","text":"Mioclonus-distonía","guid":"xMp8If-A10MrCx1Y-Wnjjw","children":[{"id":"87","parent":"86","text":"• Distonía leve-moderada, afecta cuello y extremidades.","guid":"N6kHA2-WCeK4DyGGoyvtqA","children":[]},{"id":"88","parent":"86","text":"• Inicio temprano (media: 6 años).","guid":"oHi8kmjXjGP8tiQZv0OP8Q","children":[]},{"id":"89","parent":"86","text":"• Genética:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"90","parent":"89","text":"• SGCE (DYT11) en cromosoma 7q21.","guid":"p-jm7TIFKJhE3S9EIoHdcw","children":[]},{"id":"91","parent":"89","text":"• Otras mutaciones posibles (RELN, CACNA1B, TH, DYT15).","guid":"BDja_rrZC5XG0yjqFZ5riA","children":[]},{"id":"92","parent":"89","text":"• Curso variable → Generalmente benigno, pero algunos casos progresivos.","guid":"Oso9qKCoFjbAIjiOoC3d7Q","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"93","parent":"61","text":"C. Mioclonus\\Nepiléptico","guid":"soes3g9-s7G4Tk7jVXapaw","children":[{"id":"94","parent":"93","text":"• Mioclonus asociado a epilepsia.","guid":"ApNKwUWy_GY7BcWI8kyIjQ","children":[]},{"id":"95","parent":"93","text":"• Tipos:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"96","parent":"95","text":"• Como parte de una crisis epiléptica.","guid":"ZVXw4xVS5wJwdiYguIxCcw","children":[]},{"id":"97","parent":"95","text":"• Crisis mioclónica aislada.","guid":"qhM98fuiATiPjBMKvpQ7Ag","children":[]},{"id":"98","parent":"95","text":"• Uno de varios tipos de crisis en\\Nun síndrome epiléptico.","guid":"ogP6a-ZPUmMSJFh1hL0sBw","children":[]}]},{"id":"99","parent":"93","text":"• Síndromes epilépticos\\Nmioclónicos:","guid":"ZXqaIQKcqzIusmI0Xe5_eg","children":[{"id":"100","parent":"99","text":"• Infantiles:","guid":"NEeEuB1l-JjdfLzMRyH12A","children":[{"id":"101","parent":"100","text":"• Espasmos infantiles (síndrome de West).","guid":"YzB8Bmo7sGcHPj25lmhZAg","children":[]},{"id":"102","parent":"100","text":"• Epilepsia mioclónica severa infantil (síndrome de Dravet).","guid":"W4_3wMdc7EJVBXrpQBh9QQ","children":[]},{"id":"103","parent":"100","text":"• Epilepsia mioclónica benigna infantil.","guid":"UHVpzey5blBpATQkQF_COw","children":[]},{"id":"104","parent":"100","text":"• Síndrome de Doose (epilepsia mioclónica-astática).","guid":"5228KGbGGYjPiM3GTAQ6IQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"105","parent":"99","text":"• Juveniles y adultos:","guid":"ooDXO7NoSErsVucgEssd7g","children":[{"id":"106","parent":"105","text":"• Epilepsia mioclónica juvenil (JME, síndrome de Janz).","guid":"zV8KMjdG7SIeYpW1yhP6kg","children":[]},{"id":"107","parent":"105","text":"• Epilepsia mioclónica criptogénica (Aicardi).","guid":"XNTDGPfgTfOusGguvIrBaA","children":[]},{"id":"108","parent":"105","text":"• Tremor cortical mioclónico familiar con epilepsia.","guid":"yg1EEbrYUHftxqOPHGE46w","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"109","parent":"93","text":"• Mioclonus focal\\Nen epilepsia:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"110","parent":"109","text":"• Epilepsia parcial continua.","guid":"H8qiTKgWC0CZQMvq8FHxfg","children":[]},{"id":"111","parent":"109","text":"• Epilepsia fotosensible.","guid":"3TU6NUS_4EKYPqlxvDbkxQ","children":[]},{"id":"112","parent":"109","text":"• Crisis de ausencia con mioclonus leve.","guid":"mtNaWqSIgL-IgMeqyRpVYQ","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"113","parent":"61","text":"D. Mioclonus sintomático\\N(secundario)","guid":"B6yj7YMvABEOz7FJoaOtGw","children":[{"id":"114","parent":"113","text":"Causado por enfermedades\\Nneurológicas y sistémicas","guid":"Rz16djVenxDGpNCz_pcSzg","children":[{"id":"115","parent":"114","text":"• Principales\\Ncategorías:","guid":"U6z6Wm1oDAWb6VkE_B8knQ","children":[{"id":"116","parent":"115","text":"• Tóxico-metabólico y fármacos.","guid":"GSQOiDXUPocwt4FF4pEe_g","children":[]},{"id":"117","parent":"115","text":"• Encefalopatías (hipoxia, metabólicas, infecciosas).","guid":"AvgjKEcrN26cRJi5VcWRhg","children":[]},{"id":"118","parent":"115","text":"• Enfermedades neurodegenerativas.","guid":"VRL0FXCwxBGI4_milJA_ew","children":[]},{"id":"119","parent":"115","text":"• Lesiones focales del sistema nervioso.","guid":"jnOwl9WoDTnM9swPSGXsJw","children":[]},{"id":"120","parent":"115","text":"• Epilepsia mioclónica progresiva.","guid":"TXfveykkp9BMEJxEqPrYZw","children":[]},{"id":"121","parent":"115","text":"• Ataxia mioclónica progresiva.","guid":"LIGzRMWlBbQ9q9jwI5TLTw","children":[]},{"id":"122","parent":"115","text":"• Síndromes postinfecciosos (ej. opsoclonus-mioclonus).","guid":"eBJ9ddzGasf7T3pcrzEz0w","children":[]},{"id":"123","parent":"115","text":"• Trastornos autoinmunes.","guid":"2U3pdJKXbOPVZe2M-vwKKQ","children":[]},{"id":"124","parent":"115","text":"• Alteraciones metabólicas y mitocondriales.","guid":"hpZLaX4W9zvA8LP80g_zhg","children":[]},{"id":"125","parent":"115","text":"• Trastornos del almacenamiento lisosomal.","guid":"ZuTSk6hmmROBNXmnhePFiA","children":[]},{"id":"126","parent":"115","text":"• Síndromes de sobresalto exagerado.","guid":"bik5wLjpNQMe7GsW3hTLXA","children":[]},{"id":"127","parent":"115","text":"• Mioclonus psicógeno.","guid":"SzbVEf3XZtllAQS5OJ5pyA","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"128","parent":"61","text":"E. Mioclonus\\Nprimario progresivo","guid":"LrKsxnZnYFoMwupzrsURow","children":[{"id":"129","parent":"128","text":"• Forma aislada y progresiva en adultos mayores.","guid":"PHFiVA_zTG-_A9yHecLDxw","children":[]},{"id":"130","parent":"128","text":"• Fisiología cortical con rasgos reflejos variables.","guid":"FGflsjZhQ98xIEOvH9Di4Q","children":[]},{"id":"131","parent":"128","text":"• Etiología incierta → Posible síndrome neurodegenerativo heterogéneo.","guid":"08bnIkH8rxfTLrEW_PBvwQ","children":[]},{"id":"132","parent":"128","text":"• Curso progresivo, aunque puede estabilizarse en estadios avanzados.","guid":"fGQzKoEeDa4weSCkYLQ59g","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"128","text":"Mioclonus\\Ncortical familiar","guid":"Nih1EcutU6_f-XRIhhw7Xw","children":[{"id":"134","parent":"133","text":"• Autosómico dominante.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"135","parent":"133","text":"• Inicio entre 20-70 años.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"136","parent":"133","text":"• Progresión lenta → Discapacidad tardía.","guid":"7hB-_yNTPb_DWOir374h_A","children":[]},{"id":"137","parent":"133","text":"• Mioclonus multifocal evocado por estímulos.","guid":"zOSADha0kasiDZWWVUYKew","children":[]},{"id":"138","parent":"133","text":"• Gen asociado: NOL3 (en población menonita canadiense).","guid":"FB4MgEpV1-9WSCSLCZdJIQ","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"139","parent":"0","text":"Evaluación del\\Nmioclonus","guid":"16jczFWDYUj4Ky7-IMJPHA","children":[{"id":"140","parent":"139","text":"1. Enfoque diagnóstico","guid":"5Am89Ako1w55CkC2VHPF_w","children":[{"id":"141","parent":"140","text":"→ Cuatro pasos clave\\Nen la evaluación","guid":"ZC6PlY0yKdXOvoueo-GqxQ","children":[{"id":"142","parent":"141","text":"1️⃣ Identificación del síndrome (según características clínicas).","guid":"NHUe4iyBSQJPQAD7a9jrfA","children":[]},{"id":"143","parent":"141","text":"2️⃣ Estudios de laboratorio complementarios.","guid":"WSEnhqTHzPhGrL0Sirsu8Q","children":[]},{"id":"144","parent":"141","text":"3️⃣ Neurofisiología clínica.","guid":"wHj4ePNT8KAQRnJRuySX7Q","children":[]},{"id":"145","parent":"141","text":"4️⃣ Pruebas para causas raras.","guid":"l6l9yatCjivyHyaq_HkP2A","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"146","parent":"139","text":"2. Identificación\\Ndel síndrome","guid":"HuhkzztuYTiggyWTdml9vg","children":[{"id":"147","parent":"146","text":"📌 Historia clínica y examen\\Nfísico → Identificación del\\Ntipo de mioclonus","guid":"n0_nNemsIljrNQYz-o4jFA","children":[{"id":"148","parent":"147","text":"• Distribución:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"149","parent":"148","text":"• Focal.","guid":"Mj51DrZpM1oYZbaztxvYqg","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"148","text":"• Multifocal (puede ser bilateral y sincrónico).","guid":"fJJeYvAc_APxQje7P9zYqg","children":[]},{"id":"151","parent":"148","text":"• Segmentario.","guid":"Ize1PY9A4aeqT3rcHh4jfA","children":[]},{"id":"152","parent":"148","text":"• Generalizado.","guid":"-BYGID-ynaTEIKzYigeyoA","children":[]}]},{"id":"153","parent":"147","text":"• Perfil temporal:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"154","parent":"153","text":"• Continuo vs intermitente.","guid":"tZXv-niBV5Um14iOzGTq7w","children":[]},{"id":"155","parent":"153","text":"• Rítmico vs irregular.","guid":"sMyu9CRtZSJsyem5Utq4AQ","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"153","text":"• Aislado vs en ráfagas repetitivas.","guid":"eeVTq9tUKnLrHeDhM2KuDQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"157","parent":"147","text":"• Activación:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"158","parent":"157","text":"• Espontáneo (en reposo).","guid":"YCEOwxgACG0oFUe2VHK-DA","children":[]},{"id":"159","parent":"157","text":"• Reflejo (inducido por estímulos).","guid":"08-D05l4wwEWCdt54qaFgQ","children":[]},{"id":"160","parent":"157","text":"• De acción (inducido por movimiento voluntario).","guid":"g1xGUWrThaJhuhNQ9XVEVA","children":[]},{"id":"161","parent":"157","text":"• Mixto (combinación de los anteriores).","guid":"5DbidO-YDaL680XMYrRFcg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"162","parent":"146","text":"🛑 Diagnóstico diferencial → Diferenciar\\Nde otros movimientos involuntarios","guid":"dUFrdbO-LRW6lveXUFjNdw","children":[{"id":"163","parent":"162","text":"• Corea.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"162","text":"• Distonía.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"165","parent":"162","text":"• Temblor.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"166","parent":"162","text":"• Tics (son estereotipados y semivoluntarios).","guid":"5YTNqFCrelowon4VehdspQ","children":[]},{"id":"167","parent":"162","text":"💡 Estudios neurofisiológicos pueden ayudar si hay dudas.","guid":"p9axlHNhhFzc6mp0WXbieQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"168","parent":"146","text":"🔎 Búsqueda de\\Ncausas tratables","guid":"wJR6MYlDArT-Aqyzgz-pdg","children":[{"id":"169","parent":"168","text":"• Mioclonus inducido por fármacos o tóxicos (se revierte al suspender el agente).","guid":"qzMxB7E5LEs9e-lYhRveYg","children":[]},{"id":"170","parent":"168","text":"• Fármacos\\Nasociados:","guid":"jsHeWtNx6AYbOXwrIXQydA","children":[{"id":"171","parent":"170","text":"• Levodopa.","guid":"N90l8xY_leiD8ClmCmlghw","children":[]},{"id":"172","parent":"170","text":"• Antidepresivos tricíclicos, ISRS, IMAO, litio.","guid":"KpgrMArhfcCyWuvNXSCXPA","children":[]},{"id":"173","parent":"170","text":"• Antibióticos (penicilinas, cefalosporinas, quinolonas).","guid":"Z7wHn5kk_xfT0GXTCFEqYA","children":[]},{"id":"174","parent":"170","text":"• Narcóticos.","guid":"j4OYmb6xEO-tV7U4zzo6fw","children":[]},{"id":"175","parent":"170","text":"• Anticonvulsivantes.","guid":"RfldGXcLmKvXAelHKevvIg","children":[]},{"id":"176","parent":"170","text":"• Anestésicos.","guid":"kNmnBtw4IsgwlzbvGuyIDw","children":[]},{"id":"177","parent":"170","text":"• Medios de contraste.","guid":"lvM8uarcpHdaY6J3LcgJdA","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"170","text":"• Bloqueadores de canales de calcio, antiarrítmicos.","guid":"f5FQNjSySrNLHik_9R-hYQ","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"170","text":"• Abstinencia de sedantes.","guid":"SBR3Ik1X81WMxSsFfEAiaw","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"180","parent":"139","text":"3. Estudios\\Ncomplementarios","guid":"-nr2huMQPNEmiLwF9k0BzA","children":[{"id":"181","parent":"180","text":"📌 Indicados si la etiología no es clara tras la evaluación inicial.","guid":"Ki5aQH2Xxut7mE8OfurYhg","children":[]},{"id":"182","parent":"180","text":"🔬 Laboratorio","guid":"5dnejEWOoL9RTLj4rkSBRw","children":[{"id":"183","parent":"182","text":"• Electrolitos: Na, K, Ca, Mg.","guid":"gVYjGfoyCybP_LNfrDGgLw","children":[]},{"id":"184","parent":"182","text":"• Glucosa.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"185","parent":"182","text":"• Función renal y hepática.","guid":"e7wGonaqtsDwgi9FJf5Urg","children":[]},{"id":"186","parent":"182","text":"• Pruebas tiroideas y anticuerpos antitiroideos.","guid":"9ipFAQ5_gb4sNMrFB6itbg","children":[]},{"id":"187","parent":"182","text":"• Paraneoplásicos (panel completo).","guid":"FgqIb23u19b15Jjba1GBaw","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"182","text":"• Vitamina E.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"189","parent":"182","text":"• Screening de drogas y tóxicos (según sospecha clínica).","guid":"vHy82VvYo_gi7d2md8vCrw","children":[]}]},{"id":"190","parent":"180","text":"🧠 Neuroimagen","guid":"kG0lCi1Lk_h2ZR_qTCEdNg","children":[{"id":"191","parent":"190","text":"• RM cerebral → Lesiones estructurales.","guid":"OHDffMSWSw8irMUCFfJHVw","children":[]},{"id":"192","parent":"190","text":"• RM medular → Si mioclonus segmentario o focal.","guid":"2J5KIERBCixYLQZkVnBeMw","children":[]}]},{"id":"193","parent":"180","text":"🦠 Descartar infecciones o\\Nenfermedades inflamatorias","guid":"0hY6aLwgcNqiqHueWw-c7g","children":[{"id":"194","parent":"193","text":"• Hemograma, PCR/VSG.","guid":"tTugdBDF-Vw7YfgayMLPAA","children":[]},{"id":"195","parent":"193","text":"• Urocultivo.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"196","parent":"193","text":"• Radiografía de tórax.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"197","parent":"193","text":"• Punción lumbar (según sospecha).","guid":"ROZgUt-atDPqu--tnHOkYw","children":[]}]},{"id":"198","parent":"180","text":"📌 Indicaciones de\\Nanálisis de LCR","guid":"1FegkJBdmgXFy4OiWiwAdw","children":[{"id":"199","parent":"198","text":"• Encefalopatía.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"200","parent":"198","text":"• Sospecha de infección.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"201","parent":"198","text":"• Sospecha de enfermedad inmune.","guid":"d7muGJghCfr6J0P4l9DC3g","children":[]},{"id":"202","parent":"198","text":"• Sospecha de enfermedad priónica (ej. Creutzfeldt-Jakob).","guid":"1a7A4zzMRHdMUJ8oVt5HKg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"203","parent":"139","text":"4. Neurofisiología\\Nclínica","guid":"npQ6KuojwMU97vFpscUNjg","children":[{"id":"204","parent":"203","text":"🔎 Si la etiología aún no está clara, estos estudios pueden ayudar a clasificar el mioclonus.","guid":"nFVrbsVvQ2_fTmDi5UwAPA","children":[]},{"id":"205","parent":"203","text":"📌 Técnicas\\Nprincipales","guid":"FchzKLaDF7_2ceoxkxBCgw","children":[{"id":"206","parent":"205","text":"• Electromiografía (EMG) de superficie → Duración y patrón de descargas musculares.","guid":"txr14bA3sUzLVYwEGkrS6A","children":[]},{"id":"207","parent":"205","text":"• EEG-EMG simultáneo → Correlación entre actividad EEG y mioclonus.","guid":"P-gWU9lCKwp_Ks_AO2CjaA","children":[]},{"id":"208","parent":"205","text":"• Potenciales evocados somatosensoriales (SEPs) → Evaluación de vías corticales.","guid":"eBgfxThIznLQkj8hNfMeMA","children":[]},{"id":"209","parent":"205","text":"• Jerk-locked averaging → Relación temporal entre EEG y EMG.","guid":"Mg_7qrvPsATeLyPOsAHIfQ","children":[]},{"id":"210","parent":"205","text":"• Reflejos de latencia larga (C-reflex) → Identifica mioclonus cortical reflejo.","guid":"W86h51znYM8S7BckB8ieVg","children":[]}]},{"id":"211","parent":"203","text":"📌 Hallazgos según\\Ntipo de mioclonus","guid":"dIVr2En600T6Mq_HL4pWTA","children":[{"id":"212","parent":"211","text":"Tipo Hallazgos\\Nen EEG/EMG","guid":"vM1pSS8XN3CpTqBXH4jpxA","children":[{"id":"213","parent":"212","text":"Cortical EEG con descargas focales (<75 ms), SEPs gigantes, C-reflex aumentado.","guid":"X1MdRCtavM_YIbC1w5H92g","children":[]},{"id":"214","parent":"212","text":"Córtico-subcortical EEG con descargas difusas (<100 ms), correlación EEG-EMG.","guid":"kBxnbUKtA5HONEljVi8oxA","children":[]},{"id":"215","parent":"212","text":"Subcortical-no segmentario No hay correlación EEG-EMG, SEPs normales, respuesta EMG a sonidos.","guid":"2Akc3wRyCq3HVoOP86mIVg","children":[]},{"id":"216","parent":"212","text":"Segmentario Descargas EMG rítmicas (>100 ms), respuesta refleja corta.","guid":"0XGyDKCPtyIVa7jmMRMFnQ","children":[]},{"id":"217","parent":"212","text":"Periférico EMG variable e irregular, sin correlación EEG.","guid":"pL5igkPGH9b2QeydAnW5Pg","children":[]}]}]}]},{"id":"218","parent":"139","text":"5. Evaluación de\\Ncausas raras","guid":"tmmOCffaRfjkw03n_kenaA","children":[{"id":"219","parent":"218","text":"📌 Si no hay diagnóstico tras\\Nestudios iniciales y\\Nneurofisiológicos, considerar:","guid":"z5jnm2V84onhiz63zVTekw","children":[{"id":"220","parent":"219","text":"• Cáncer oculto (screening paraneoplásico + imagenología).","guid":"JEVixZh3UHaMftwr7k8bxg","children":[]},{"id":"221","parent":"219","text":"• Malabsorción (celiaquía, enfermedad de Whipple).","guid":"hlD6TYhVAs-5Xtsw8pNe6A","children":[]},{"id":"222","parent":"219","text":"• Errores congénitos\\Ndel metabolismo:","guid":"bc58nQAAGj0f-HB0JxSfFQ","children":[{"id":"223","parent":"222","text":"• Déficit de neuraminidasa (sialidosis).","guid":"z23fw_3TF1DCI42hU0gAYQ","children":[]},{"id":"224","parent":"222","text":"• Déficit de biotinidasa (deficiencia de carboxilasas múltiples).","guid":"bS6hMVdBe_f49EurH_gvUw","children":[]}]},{"id":"225","parent":"219","text":"• Enfermedades\\Nmetabólicas heredadas:","guid":"","children":[{"id":"226","parent":"225","text":"• Enfermedad de Wilson (cobre, anillos de Kayser-Fleischer).","guid":"36UpkM7-xhuufI-aWtQXCQ","children":[]},{"id":"227","parent":"225","text":"• Ataxia-telangiectasia.","guid":"lzQ7LmwmSz8QlxgOJEqqGQ","children":[]},{"id":"228","parent":"225","text":"• Epilepsia mioclónica progresiva (Unverricht-Lundborg, Lafora).","guid":"Q95LnavVYOUQkMoVKvzzzg","children":[]},{"id":"229","parent":"225","text":"• Trastornos mitocondriales (lactato, biopsia muscular, genética).","guid":"PHiL4ktqBpti_R0gNSByfA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"230","parent":"218","text":"📌 Importante","guid":"sA_DnrVCrV0GYTSNOqPgrQ","children":[{"id":"231","parent":"230","text":"• Screening paraneoplásico es más costo-efectivo que imagenología extensa.","guid":"E5Q-HIgD0wXqudn8rd7osw","children":[]},{"id":"232","parent":"230","text":"• Mioclonus opsoclonus en niños → Evaluar neuroblastoma, aun si anticuerpos paraneoplásicos son negativos.","guid":"Knm643ivAiHLoQWFe2j1kg","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"233","parent":"139","text":"6. Evaluación en\\Npacientes hospitalizados","guid":"tuF0UCCuMNZQnR9eP2bDqQ","children":[{"id":"234","parent":"233","text":"📌 Causas más frecuentes\\Nen hospitalizados","guid":"vbcl4nRJkNe-xF4VeBNiTw","children":[{"id":"235","parent":"234","text":"• Mioclonus tóxico-metabólico.","guid":"bcRaffU5V8vnu7Zq-TqUSA","children":[]},{"id":"236","parent":"234","text":"• Inducido por fármacos.","guid":"","children":[]},{"id":"237","parent":"234","text":"• Condiciones neurológicas agudas/subagudas.","guid":"RBjlZ2cdBMqIGTbaVyuxwg","children":[]}]},{"id":"238","parent":"233","text":"→ En estos casos, la prioridad es descartar causas reversibles rápidamente.","guid":"52kBhgGITZEHdYJL-HbzyQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"239","parent":"139","text":"7. Resumen del\\Nenfoque diagnóstico","guid":"-l8xvJJBaJ7n512yL-uKJA","children":[{"id":"240","parent":"239","text":"🔎 Pasos\\Nclaves","guid":"SVYq78zEFqZC5Hcbf5T5fQ","children":[{"id":"241","parent":"240","text":"1️⃣ Historia y examen físico → Determinar tipo de mioclonus y descartar fármacos/toxinas.","guid":"6Aydk_mPSTJR3lYzUGCP6Q","children":[]},{"id":"242","parent":"240","text":"2️⃣ Laboratorio y neuroimagen → Identificar causas metabólicas, inflamatorias o estructurales.","guid":"gZZeKOldGRWLgTJlOF7MfA","children":[]},{"id":"243","parent":"240","text":"3️⃣ Neurofisiología → Clasificar el mioclonus según su origen anatómico.","guid":"9sXMvcffnejaiOe-eyUN9Q","children":[]},{"id":"244","parent":"240","text":"4️⃣ Evaluación de causas raras → Si diagnóstico aún no está claro, buscar síndromes específicos.","guid":"tx5mLdggzFlkeNV0Mhy7cA","children":[]}]},{"id":"245","parent":"239","text":"✅ Diagnóstico preciso permite un tratamiento dirigido según la etiología.","guid":"U49bvjUhIG7_oewCE3k22g","children":[]}]}]}]},"node_count":245,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"General","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Neurología","filename":"UTD. Mioclonias-2025","id":"map_1461","resolved_references":[]}